# Where to find project rules

## Desired state

**Cursor** loads rule files from `rules/**` and `.cursor/rules/**` according to `globs` and `alwaysApply`. Authors edit the **canonical** files under `rules/`; this file is a short **pointer** to avoid duplicating long content.

## Properties

- **P1 (canonical path)**: Normative content lives in `rules/{NN-category}/*.mdc` (see [0-rules-structure.mdc](../00-architecture/0-rules-structure.mdc)).
- **P2 (stack-specific overview)**: For NestJS vertical-slice work, see [3-nestjs-architecture.mdc](../03-frameworks-and-libraries/3-nestjs-architecture.mdc) and rules R1–R7 linked there.
- **P3 (agnostic architecture)**: [0-vertical-slices.mdc](../00-architecture/0-vertical-slices.mdc), [0-hexagonal-ddd.mdc](../00-architecture/0-hexagonal-ddd.mdc), and related `00-*` files define language-independent structure.
- **P4 (SpecKit)**: Constitution and plan memory, when present, align with the same structure; do not contradict [5-spec-driven-dev.mdc](../05-workflows-and-processes/5-spec-driven-dev.mdc).

## Skill References

- [spec-reindex](../../skills/spec-reindex/SKILL.md) for index repair when the skill exists
- [npm-private-registry](../../skills/npm-private-registry/SKILL.md) for private package setup

## Enforcement

- **Detect**: Copy-pasted stack tables in multiple meta files; broken relative links after moves.
- **Fix**: One pointer file; link to `rules/` only.
